Title: Breaking the Sorting Barrier for Directed Single-Source Shortest Paths
Description: We give a deterministic $O(m\log^{2/3}n)$-time algorithm for single-source shortest paths (SSSP) on directed graphs with real non-negative edge weights in the comparison-addition model. This is the first result to break the $O(m+n\log n)$ time bound of Dijkstra's algorithm on sparse graphs, showing that Dijkstra's algorithm is not optimal for SSSP.

Title: Getting Gemini to write an ORM for Spanner in a weekend
Description: Recently, I wanted to get a Bun application working with Google Spanner. While Google provides a client library for Spanner (@google-cloud/spanner), the JavaScript (Node.js/Bun) ecosystem lacks a dedicated Object-Relational Mapper (ORM) specifically designed for Spanner‚Äôs native Google SQL dialect. This gap prompted an experiment: could Google‚Äôs Gemini assist in rapidly developing one? This post details that journey and introduces spanner-orm, a Google SQL ORM in Bun largely created with AI help over a weekend.
